<span id="freeTextContainer7682712052364910777">I read this book back when it first appeared. It is a bit of a slog but I still remember the story today and I have not found an account of the enhanced colonial acquisition of Africa leading up to WW1 that surpasses this book, although there are fine accounts for particular people and regions. I remember few books as I do this one.</span>

